Duquesne University Alumni Association

For some, the Duquesne experience is a cherished family legacy; for others, it started with a visit as a high school student. Some complete online programs without ever setting foot on campus. More important than when or where it began is the fact that it never ends.
Duquesne is always with you, in the distinctive ruby ring, in the academic foundation for your professional career, and most of all, in the Spiritan values of respect for -- and service to -- others that you live each day.
The mission of the Office of Alumni Engagement is to create opportunities for alumni to foster lifelong engagement, affinity and pride within the Duquesne community to further the mission of the University.
We invite you to stay connected with the University community, attend alumni events, share your time and talent as a volunteer, and make a gift to support the aspects of Duquesne that mean the most to you.









Registration is now open for Homecoming & Reunion Weekend!


Connect with the Alumni Association
Network with alumni, view photos of campus and see the latest campus and alumni events on our social media pages!






















Office of Alumni Engagement

                    

                    

1 Mezzanine Libermann Hall 

                    600 Forbes Avenue

Pittsburgh, PA 15282                        

                        Email: alumnionline@duq.edu 

                    Phone: 412.396.6209




